about.description: This package allows you to authenticate to AWS with Amazon's signature version 4 signing process with the python requests library. Tested with both python 2.7 and 3.
about.summary: AWS signature version 4 signing process for the python requests module

name: aws-requests-auth
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "aws-requests-auth" %}
{% set version = "0.4.2" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 112c85fe938a01e28f7e1a87168615b6977b28596362b1dcbafbf4f2cc69f720

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv "

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - requests >=0.14.0
  run:
    - python
    - requests >=0.14.0

test:
  imports:
    - aws_requests_auth

about:
  home: https://github.com/davidmuller/aws-requests-auth
  license: BSD
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: AWS signature version 4 signing process for the python requests module
  description:
    This package allows you to authenticate to AWS with Amazon's signature version 4 signing process with the python requests library.
    Tested with both python 2.7 and 3.
  doc_url: https://github.com/DavidMuller/aws-requests-auth/blob/master/README.md
  dev_url: https://github.com/DavidMuller/aws-requests-auth

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - danieljahn
